summary:
WHAT’S HAPPENIN’ YA CLOWNS?
Let’s get fuckin’ WEEEEEEIRD for a minute. Let’s go into almost conspiracy levels of off the deep...
body:
WHAT’S HAPPENIN’ YA CLOWNS?

Let’s get fuckin’ WEEEEEEIRD for a minute. Let’s go into almost conspiracy levels of off the deep end!

Okay, that was a weird way to start this up, but hear me out! I got something both kinda funny, kinda weird, and kinda…worthy of fan-art-ish.

I’ve joked before, in regards to Aggretsuko, that Retsuko’s death metal voice should’ve instead been done by Alissa White-Gluz, the current vocalist for Swedish melodic death metal band Arch Enemy.

If you wanna good glimpse of what she sounds like, here’s a music video from their most recent album: https://youtu.be/lk2-bgwA0Ro

So, at first, I just left it at that. Seemed like a silly joke, yet cool idea. Then, just a few weeks ago, I was browsing Instagram (heh, how fitting, knowing the show, eh?), and just randomly came across Alissa’s page….and I found out something that hit me like a freight train.

She’s actually going out with Doyle Wolfgang von Frankenstein, the guitarist for the band, The Misfits.

The Misfits are a horror punk band.

Horror punk.

Punk.

So, like, female death metal singer, in a relationship with a guitarist of a punk band.

To add to that, not only can he play guitar…

He can play bass too.

Not to mention:

He’s a bit of a tall, sulky dude.

Almost like…

H-hold on a minute, I-

W-WAIT A GODDAMN SEC-

summary: So I finally got around to remembering I had the Aggretsuko candy bar after the midst of a PMS-induced chocolate craving. Rest...
body:
So I finally got around to remembering I had the Aggretsuko candy bar after the midst of a PMS-induced chocolate craving. Rest assured I just took a bite…for now. (ﾉ´ヮ`)ﾉ*: ･ﾟ💝🍫 It’s a nice and tangy ( albeit bland in terms of the chocolate itself) wrapped in gold foil that was produced by the Chocolate Lab in Hollywood! Right next to the Chinese Theater.

Weight: 6 oz

Ingredients: Dark chocolate infused with chocolate hazelnut cream, potato chips, chili powder and sea salt. Mildly bitter sweet/ tangy flavor.

The design is super lovely! 💖 However, I wish they added indent lines on the bar so you could break off the pieces neatly. Overall, I can understand the price ( $8 USD ) because its made from a luxury choco brand in Hollywood. But still, I wish they had more variation for candies for her.

summary: Now that you finished the wedding arch,  what is next for you?
question: Now that you finished the wedding arch,  what is next for you?
answer:
That’s actually a very good question! If I am to be an honest man, I don’t have one specific thing set. I plan on a few things to go on.


In regards to fanfictions, and in particular, The Ikariverse, I plan on writing some one-shots, just as a way to keep folks entertained, without having to wait for multiple parts that take me months to write. I do hope this next one I’m starting up will actually be a collab with a dear friend of mine….I just gotta, ya know, send it to him. :3

The big elephant in the room will definitely be Season 2. For the record, I do not intend on it being something that happens in The Ikariverse. Not because I am against what happens in it, but because I feel it will lead to a bunch of inconsistencies that I will need to re-work. Like I said, I already had to retcon a thing or two just to get the Christmas Special in, I don’t want to do that for a whole season.

Also…I probably won’t be immediately watching it when it comes out. 😅


Mainly due to work (I have a job now, yay!), but also due to my own personal…stress, I guess? With what happens in it. I kinda just plan on shutting off notifications about it when it gets around that time. Once things have blown over slightly, I’ll ask another good friend of mine a question or two about what happens in it (mostly regarding Retsuaida, which is probably gonna be found dead in Miami 🙃), and then get back in the swing of things. Of course, that would mean spoilers, but truthfully, I was never one against that. Especially for something as kinda nerve-wracking as this. So if you want to ask me what I thought of the season…um…I’ll get back to you later. Hopefully y’all understand.

And don’t worry, wittle Ikari ain’t going anywhere. I still plan on writing the wacky adventures of the weird little family. And if the epilogue is anything to go by, it may very well get bigger! 😉


Actually, the hell am I saying, it IS gonna get bigger. I kinda plan on Ikari getting a little sister. That’s literally all I have for that, tho.


Was this a bit too big? I dunno. But I hope it answered your question! 😃

trail.content:
That’s actually a very good question! If I am to be an honest man, I don’t have one specific thing set. I plan on a few things to go on.


In regards to fanfictions, and in particular, The Ikariverse, I plan on writing some one-shots, just as a way to keep folks entertained, without having to wait for multiple parts that take me months to write. I do hope this next one I’m starting up will actually be a collab with a dear friend of mine….I just gotta, ya know, send it to him. :3

The big elephant in the room will definitely be Season 2. For the record, I do not intend on it being something that happens in The Ikariverse. Not because I am against what happens in it, but because I feel it will lead to a bunch of inconsistencies that I will need to re-work. Like I said, I already had to retcon a thing or two just to get the Christmas Special in, I don’t want to do that for a whole season.

Also…I probably won’t be immediately watching it when it comes out. 😅


Mainly due to work (I have a job now, yay!), but also due to my own personal…stress, I guess? With what happens in it. I kinda just plan on shutting off notifications about it when it gets around that time. Once things have blown over slightly, I’ll ask another good friend of mine a question or two about what happens in it (mostly regarding Retsuaida, which is probably gonna be found dead in Miami 🙃), and then get back in the swing of things. Of course, that would mean spoilers, but truthfully, I was never one against that. Especially for something as kinda nerve-wracking as this.
